<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><title>Isaac Freund's Poetry</title><link href="https://isaacfreund.com/poetry/"/><link rel="self" href="https://isaacfreund.com/poetry/feed.xml" type="application/atom+xml"/><id>https://isaacfreund.com/poetry/feed.xml</id><author><name>Isaac Freund</name><email>mail@isaacfreund.com</email></author><updated>2025-03-30T00:00:00Z</updated><entry><title>Diametric Forces</title><link href="https://isaacfreund.com/poetry/diametric-forces/"/><id>https://isaacfreund.com/poetry/diametric-forces/</id><published>2025-03-30T00:00:00Z</published><updated>2025-03-30T00:00:00Z</updated><content type="html">&lt;div class="poem">&lt;p>&lt;span>wintergreen&lt;br>&lt;/span>&lt;span>summer sheen&lt;br>&lt;/span>&lt;span>walk among the roses&lt;/span>&lt;/p>&lt;p>&lt;span>old and new&lt;br>&lt;/span>&lt;span>out of view&lt;br>&lt;/span>&lt;span>have forgot what once was&lt;/span>&lt;/p>&lt;p>&lt;span>fleeting thought&lt;br>&lt;/span>&lt;span>won't be caught&lt;br>&lt;/span>&lt;span>suffering my choices&lt;/span>&lt;/p>&lt;p>&lt;span>feeling seen&lt;br>&lt;/span>&lt;span>in a dream&lt;br>&lt;/span>&lt;span>diametric forces&lt;/span>&lt;/p>&lt;/div></content></entry><entry><title>Strawberry Sweet</title><link href="https://isaacfreund.com/poetry/strawberry-sweet/"/><id>https://isaacfreund.com/poetry/strawberry-sweet/</id><published>2024-05-25T00:00:00Z</published><updated>2024-05-25T00:00:00Z</updated><content type="html">&lt;div class="poem">&lt;p>&lt;span>when summer's starting&lt;br>&lt;/span>&lt;span>and we are eating strawberries&lt;br>&lt;/span>&lt;span>you kiss me&lt;br>&lt;/span>&lt;span>and it is sweet&lt;/span>&lt;/p>&lt;p>&lt;span>when rain is pouring&lt;br>&lt;/span>&lt;span>and bed is so inviting&lt;br>&lt;/span>&lt;span>in your arms&lt;br>&lt;/span>&lt;span>I feel complete&lt;/span>&lt;/p>&lt;p>&lt;span>when times are trying&lt;br>&lt;/span>&lt;span>and life is falling out of balance&lt;br>&lt;/span>&lt;span>I am glad&lt;br>&lt;/span>&lt;span>that we did meet&lt;/span>&lt;/p>&lt;p>&lt;span>when summer's ending&lt;br>&lt;/span>&lt;span>and there are no more strawberries&lt;br>&lt;/span>&lt;span>you kiss me&lt;br>&lt;/span>&lt;span>and it is sweet&lt;/span>&lt;/p>&lt;/div></content></entry><entry><title>Mossy Boughs</title><link href="https://isaacfreund.com/poetry/mossy-boughs/"/><id>https://isaacfreund.com/poetry/mossy-boughs/</id><published>2024-03-30T00:00:00Z</published><updated>2024-03-30T00:00:00Z</updated><content type="html">&lt;div class="poem">&lt;p>&lt;span>like green furry fingers&lt;br>&lt;/span>&lt;span>grasping at air&lt;br>&lt;/span>&lt;span>the floor below&lt;br>&lt;/span>&lt;span>thick with dead leaves of the past&lt;br>&lt;/span>&lt;span>and there above&lt;br>&lt;/span>&lt;span>soft green ones emerging&lt;/span>&lt;/p>&lt;p>&lt;span>storm&lt;br>&lt;/span>&lt;span>a tree falls&lt;br>&lt;/span>&lt;span>and takes its neighbor with it&lt;br>&lt;/span>&lt;span>seasons later&lt;br>&lt;/span>&lt;span>their children rise to take their place&lt;/span>&lt;/p>&lt;p>&lt;span>eons pass&lt;br>&lt;/span>&lt;span>the sun dims and darkens&lt;br>&lt;/span>&lt;span>life slows and ceases&lt;br>&lt;/span>&lt;span>what now?&lt;/span>&lt;/p>&lt;/div></content></entry></feed>